<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Disch]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-03-06T07:56:55-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-03-06T07:56:55-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4919&amp;p=43943#p43943</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4919&amp;p=43943#p43943"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mappers and .NES file layout]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4919&amp;p=43943#p43943"><![CDATA[
iNES layout is simple:<br /><br />- $10 byte header<br />- optional $200 byte trainer (typically absent)<br />- X*$4000 PRG-ROM banks<br />- X*$2000 CHR-ROM banks<br /><br />The number of PRG and CHR banks is indicated in the header, as well as whether or not the trainer exists.<br /><br />Like tokumaru said ... there's no such thing as a bank which can/can't be swapped into X.  The mapper simply uses the selected (swapped in) page number to fill in the high bits of the address when it reads from the ROM chip.  Therefore:<br /><br />If dealing with 16K PRG banks:<br /><br />bank 0 = offset 0x00010-0x0400F<br />bank 1 = offset 0x04010-0x0800F<br />bank 2 = offset 0x08010-0x0C00F<br />... etc<br /><br />Or if dealing with 8K PRG banks:<br /><br />bank 0 = 0x00010 - 0x0200F<br />bank 1 = 0x02010 - 0x0400F<br />bank 2 = 0x04010 - 0x0600F<br />... etc<br /><br />(note:  offsets assume no trainer)<br /><br />CHR works the same way.<br /><br />Any bank can be swapped to anywhere, the mapper doesn't care (with a few rare exceptions which are always noted in documentation)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Fri Mar 06, 2009 7:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
